FAQStory.answer: To rent a car, you will need a valid driver's license, a credit card in your name, and a government-issued photo ID (such as a passport or national ID). International renters may also need to present an International Driving Permit (IDP) in addition to their home country driver's license.
FAQStory.question: What documents do I need to rent a car?

FAQStory.answer: The minimum age to rent a car is typically 21 years old. However, renters under 25 may be subject to a young driver surcharge. Some luxury or specialty vehicles may have a higher minimum age requirement of 25 or even 30 years old. Age requirements may vary by location and vehicle type.
FAQStory.question: What is the minimum age to rent a car?

FAQStory.answer: If you need to cancel your reservation, you can do so through our website or mobile app by accessing your account and selecting the booking you wish to cancel. Cancellations made at least 48 hours before the scheduled pickup time typically receive a full refund. Cancellations made less than 48 hours in advance may be subject to a cancellation fee.
FAQStory.question: How do I cancel my car rental reservation?

FAQStory.answer: Yes, most of our locations allow you to pick up a car at one location and return it to another, which is known as a one-way rental. Please note that one-way rentals may incur an additional fee, which varies depending on the distance between locations and the specific vehicle. You can select this option during the booking process.
FAQStory.question: Can I pick up the car at one location and return it to another?

FAQStory.answer: We offer various insurance options to protect you during your rental period. These typically include Collision Damage Waiver (CDW), Theft Protection (TP), Personal Accident Insurance (PAI), and Supplemental Liability Insurance (SLI). We recommend reviewing these options carefully during the booking process to select the coverage that best meets your needs.
FAQStory.question: What insurance options are available for my rental car?

FAQStory.answer: If you're involved in an accident with your rental car, first ensure everyone's safety and call emergency services if needed. Then contact our 24/7 customer service line immediately to report the incident. Document the accident by taking photos and collecting information from other involved parties. Fill out an accident report form, which can be found in the glove compartment of the vehicle.
FAQStory.question: What should I do if I have an accident with the rental car?

FAQStory.answer: Yes, most of our vehicles are equipped with GPS navigation systems. You can request this feature during the booking process for an additional daily fee. Alternatively, you can use navigation apps on your smartphone, such as Google Maps or Waze, which may be connected to the car's infotainment system via Apple CarPlay or Android Auto in newer models.
FAQStory.question: Do rental cars come with GPS navigation?

FAQStory.answer: We expect the car to be returned with the same amount of fuel it had when you picked it up, which is typically a full tank. If you return the car with less fuel, you'll be charged for the missing fuel plus a refueling service fee. We also offer a prepaid fuel option, allowing you to pay for a full tank upfront and return the car with any amount of fuel without additional charges.
FAQStory.question: What is your fuel policy for rental cars?

FAQStory.answer: Yes, most of our locations allow an additional driver to be added to the rental agreement. The additional driver must be present at the time of rental with their valid driver's license and must meet the same age and eligibility requirements as the primary driver. There may be an additional fee for extra drivers, though this fee is often waived for spouses or domestic partners.
FAQStory.question: Can someone else drive my rental car?

FAQStory.answer: If you need to extend your rental period, please contact our customer service at least 24 hours before your scheduled return time. Extensions are subject to vehicle availability and may result in a rate change. If you fail to extend your rental and return the vehicle late, you may be charged additional fees according to our late return policy.
FAQStory.question: How can I extend my car rental period?
